Hello
My first request is that the IDE ought to be based on Ocaml's abstract=
 syntax,
and that the tools dealing with the concrete syntax (such as emacs macros)=
 be
parameterized by the camlp4 grammar, so as to be adaptable to the revised
syntax as well as to the standard syntax. This is not a mere feature, it is
an important architectural design decision. This way beginners may learn the
revised syntax, while experienced users may keep the syntax they are=
 familiar=20
with.
G=E9rard Huet


